- Use this section especially when comparing tools, approaches, or configuration options

## Formatting Guidelines

- Use clear headings and subheadings
- Include code blocks with proper syntax highlighting
- Add examples for complex concepts
- Use bullet points for lists
- Include diagrams or visual aids when helpful
- Mark optional sections clearly

## Quality Checklist

- [ ] All required sections (What? and How?) are present
- [ ] Information is accurate and up-to-date
- [ ] Examples are practical and relevant
- [ ] Code blocks are properly formatted
- [ ] Language is clear and accessible
- [ ] Structure follows the 5W1H method